    "description": "NTPC is actively seeking a talented and motivated Process Engineer to join our dynamic team in Kanpur. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout NTPC:\nNTPC is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Kanpur, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with NTPC!",
